      "parent_block_plain_text": "Attention and FFN are subsets of operations in a model. In a model forward pass, attention’s output feeds into a token router, and the token router assigns each token to k experts, where each expert is an FFN. Attention and FFN have very different performance properties. During decode phase, the GPU utilization of attention barely improves when scaling batch size due to being bounded by loading KV cache. In contrast, the GPU utilization of FFN scales with batch size comparatively better.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
